ata-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1"><div class="social-share-top" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0"><div class="component-social-share default" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhappy-valley-jerry-sandusky-review&amp;t=Happy%20Valley%3A%20Penn%20State%20and%20the%20Culture%20of%20Jerry%20Sandusky&#x27;s%20Crimes" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhappy-valley-jerry-sandusky-review&amp;t=Happy%20Valley%3A%20Penn%20State%20and%20the%20Culture%20of%20Jerry%20Sandusky&#x27;s%20Crimes" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0.1">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item twitter" data-href="https://twitter.com/share?text=Happy%20Valley%3A%20Penn%20State%20and%20the%20Culture%20of%20Jerry%20Sandusky&#x27;s%20Crimes&amp;via=GQMagazine&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhappy-valley-jerry-sandusky-review" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter"><a href="https://twitter.com/share?text=Happy%20Valley%3A%20Penn%20State%20and%20the%20Culture%20of%20Jerry%20Sandusky&#x27;s%20Crimes&amp;via=GQMagazine&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhappy-valley-jerry-sandusky-review" target="_blank" aria-label="Twitter" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0.1">Twitter</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><h2 class="dek" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.3"></h2><div class="body-text" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4"><div class="embed image" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4.0"><figure class="embedded-image" data-type="image"><div class="image-content"><div class="component-rendition"><div class="component-image loaded"><span><img src="http://media.gq.com/photos/55828d59e52bc4b477a984c6/master/w_768/blogs-the-feed-jerry-sandusky-happy-valley-documentary.jpg" alt="blogs-the-feed-jerry-sandusky-happy-valley-documentary.jpg"></span></div></div><div class="component-social-share default"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhappy-valley-jerry-sandusky-review&amp;t=blogs-the-feed-jerry-sandusky-happy-valley-documentary.jpg"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhappy-valley-jerry-sandusky-review&amp;t=blogs-the-feed-jerry-sandusky-happy-valley-documentary.jpg" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item pinterest" data-href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhappy-valley-jerry-sandusky-review&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F55828d59e52bc4b477a984c6%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2Fblogs-the-feed-jerry-sandusky-happy-valley-documentary.jpg&amp;description=blogs-the-feed-jerry-sandusky-happy-valley-documentary.jpg"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhappy-valley-jerry-sandusky-review&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F55828d59e52bc4b477a984c6%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2Fblogs-the-feed-jerry-sandusky-happy-valley-documentary.jpg&amp;description=blogs-the-feed-jerry-sandusky-happy-valley-documentary.jpg" target="_blank" aria-label="Pinterest"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Pinterest</span></a></div></div></div></figure></div><p data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4.1"> Photo: Patrick Smith/Getty Images</p><p data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4.2">The creepiest found footage you&apos;re likely to see in a movie anytime soon shows a cheerful man romping with a bunch of screamingly excited children. That&apos;s because the man is Jerry Sandusky, the kids are lucky attendees at his charity camp for underprivileged tykes, and the movie is <em>Happy Valley, </em>Amir Bar-Lev&apos;s fine-toned documentary about the grisly child-predator scandal that A) sent Sandusky to prison for life, which doesn&apos;t seem nearly long enough, B) put legendary Penn State coach Joe Paterno out of job with his reputation in tatters after nearly half a century of <em>Sports Illustrated </em>godhood, and C) shattered the school&apos;s beloved status as college football&apos;s Jedi knights for, undoubtedly, years to come.</p><p data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4.3">Which of those outcomes defines your concern with the case is one of the great American Rorschasch blots. Bar-Lev&#x2014;a filmmaker uncommonly attentive to how people&apos;s perspectives express their values, as 2010&apos;s <em>The Tillman Story </em>showed&#x2014;does a terrific job of conveying that. Penn Staters won&apos;t be happy with the movie, but it&apos;s fundamentally compassionate and never badgering.</p><p data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4.5">Not, of course, that the director has any interest in mitigating Sandusky&apos;s creepiness. As you already know if you remember the perp&apos;s clueless 2011 interview with Bob Costas on NBC&apos;s <em>Rock Center, </em>which isn&apos;t included here, part of what makes him so revealing as a monster is that he&apos;s such a clod. It&apos;s almost as if being exposed as a pedophile was the first evidence he had any inner life at all, making ye olde banality of evil resonate to beat the Penn State marching band. But his m.o. wasn&apos;t what you&apos;d call improvisational, since he seems to have founded Second Mile essentially to give himself creditable-looking access to a steady supply of juvenile victims. Once an organization man, always an organization man.</p><p data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4.6">In the only scene in <em>Happy Valley </em>that shows him interacting with anyone after the scandal broke&#x2014;he&apos;s fending off a reporter who&apos;s shown up on his doorstep&#x2014;his complacent affability is more disconcerting than exasperation or twitchy panic would have been. Acting like genial, ever-obliging Jerry Sandusky, now as loyally subordinate to his lawyer as he ever was to Paterno, is the only public role he knows. He isn&apos;t about to let a minor glitch like being an accused serial child rapist reboot that familiar routine.</p><p data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4.7">However, Sandusky himself isn&apos;t Bar-Lev&apos;s only or even major focus of interest. Damn near mercifully, because the less time spent in his company the better, he grows less central as the scandal&apos;s ripple effects take hold, tainting Paterno&apos;s reputation, compromising Penn State&apos;s trustworthiness as an institution, and catapulting pretty much everyone with an emotional stake in &quot;Joe Pa,&quot; the school and/or its football team into various states of denial, pigheaded defiance, and misdirected anger.</p><p data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4.8">Nobody comes off especially well except for Matt Sandusky, Jerry&apos;s adopted son, who clinched the case against the predator when he bravely came forward midway through the trial with his own history of abuse. To a lesser extent, Scott Paterno, the less blinkered two of Joe&apos;s boys, also shows some welcome decency. Yet to Bar-Lev&apos;s credit, he isn&apos;t out to simple-mindedly condemn Penn State, the fans, or the whole culture of worship surrounding Paterno and the Nittany Lions that ended up as Sandusky&apos;s enabler. He just wants to understand it all, which is not only more humane but ultimately more, well, useful.</p><p data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4.9"><em>Happy Valley</em> wouldn&apos;t be anywhere near as haunting if it didn&apos;t catch the lyrical side of doting on a football team&#x2014;the beauty of game-day rituals, the communal identification with countless strangers, the alleviation of the rest of life&apos;s bewilderments&#x2014;along with adulation&apos;s limits as a moral guide to all the stuff we count on football for reprieves from. However foolish they may be, there&apos;s nothing ignoble about those desires. Even the cult of Joe Pa, which was and is kind of perturbing, would have been more likely to earn a &quot;yeesh&quot; instead of a &quot;yikes&quot; from outsiders if Sandusky&apos;s free ride hadn&apos;t suddenly left it looking pernicious. What Bar-Lev doesn&apos;t lose sight of is that, if the culture he depicts ended up abetting Sandusky&apos;s crimes&#x2014;and it did&#x2014;that was partly because it wasn&apos;t any more designed to deal with them than a musical comedy is to guard against velociraptor attacks.</p><p data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4.a">From Paterno to the undergrads who rioted (with spectacularly misplaced chants of &quot;Fuck the media!&quot;) when he was fired, naivete is the constant here. In however grotesque a way, even Sandusky had it. The students&apos; hysteria is often appalling&#x2014;anyone who tries to wrestle them back into remembering Sandusky&apos;s victims is resented&#x2014;but it&apos;s also poignant. Few of us react well to having our identities shredded, maybe especially when those identifies are invested in something as frivolous but, at least most of the time, morally anodyne as sports.</p><p data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4.b">Well aware that he&apos;s depicting a crisis of religious faith, Bar-Lev dwells to beautiful effect on the fate of the relics of Paterno&apos;s not-quite-secular sainthood&#x2014;the statue the administration finally took down when the NCAA voided his record from 1998 on, the campus mural that gave him pride of place and that the artist kept altering once the scandal broke. First he paints over Sandusky, then he adds a halo above Paterno&apos;s head when Joe Pa dies of cancer just three months after getting fired. Then he scrubs the halo too before figuring out a reconciliatory compromise.</p><p data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.4.c">The forlorn final version of the muralist&apos;s tribute is a heartbreaker, somehow perfect even in its inadequacy. If you&apos;re tempted to scoff, you won&apos;t be once you ask yourself just what an adequate expression of the flock&apos;s regret would look like.</p></div><div class="grid" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5"><div class="row" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0"><div class="col col-sm-15" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0"><div class="component-topics" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0"><ul data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0"><li data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-0"><a href="../search?tags=ENTERTAINMENT" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-0.0">ENTERTAINMENT</a></li><li data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-1"><a href="http://www.gq.com/search?tags=FOOTBALL" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-1.0">FOOTBALL</a></li><li data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-2"><a href="http://www.gq.com/search?tags=JERRY&#32;SANDUSKY" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-2.0">JERRY SANDUSKY</a></li><li data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-3"><a href="../search?tags=MOVIES%2520+%2520TV" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-3.0">MOVIES + TV</a></li><li data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-4"><a href="http://www.gq.com/search?tags=PENN&#32;STATE" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-4.0">PENN STATE</a></li><li data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-5"><a href="../search?tags=SPORTS" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-5.0">SPORTS</a></li><li data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-6"><a href="http://www.gq.com/search?tags=TOM&#32;CARSON" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-6.0">TOM CARSON</a></li></ul></div></div><div class="col col-sm-5" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.1"><div class="social-share-bottom" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0"><div class="component-social-share default" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhappy-valley-jerry-sandusky-review&amp;t=Happy%20Valley%3A%20Penn%20State%20and%20the%20Culture%20of%20Jerry%20Sandusky&#x27;s%20Crimes" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhappy-valley-jerry-sandusky-review&amp;t=Happy%20Valley%3A%20Penn%20State%20and%20the%20Culture%20of%20Jerry%20Sandusky&#x27;s%20Crimes" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0.1">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item twitter" data-href="https://twitter.com/share?text=Happy%20Valley%3A%20Penn%20State%20and%20the%20Culture%20of%20Jerry%20Sandusky&#x27;s%20Crimes&amp;via=GQMagazine&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fhappy-valley-jerry-sandusky-review" data-reactid=".o8uznabn5s.1.1.0.0.5.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter"><a href="https://twitter.com/share?text=Happy%20Valley%3A%20Penn%20State%20and%20the%20Culture%20of%20Jerry%20Sandusky&#x27;s%20Crimes&amp;via=GQMagazine&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fww